										<tr>
											<td><h2>Pure Maple Syrup in Eastern 
                          Ontario </h2>
                        <p><img src="images/sap.jpg" alt="frozen sap" width="180" height="135" class="img1" />The 
                          Eastern Ontario Maple Syrup Producers Association was 
                          founded to address the needs and interests of sugarmakers 
                          no matter what the size of their operation. We are one 
                          of 11 local chapters who are members of the Ontario 
                          Maple Syrup Producers Association (<a href="http://www.ontariomaple.com">OMSPA</a>), 
                          a provincial non-profit organization formed to represent 
                          syrup producers across the province. Our region of interest 
                          is from the Quebec - Ontario border to the Rideau River 
                          and Dundas County and from the St. Lawrence River in 
                          the South to the Ottawa River in the North. You may 
                          only tap 10~15 trees or maybe 5000 each season. In either 
                          case the Eastern Ontario Maple Syrup Producers Association 
                          could be a great tool for your sugarmaking operation.<strong><br>
                          </strong>We are actively seeking new members and would 
                          like to hear from you!</p>
                        <p>&nbsp; </p>				
